{
  "doc_id": "47274",
  "text": "We included all patients who underwent one or more of these procedures for any of the following diagnoses: diabetes with peripheral circulatory disorders (250.7ϫ), lower extremity arterial atherosclerosis, stenosis, thromboembolism, and/or gangrene (440.2ϫ, 400.3ϫ, 443.81, 443.9, 444. 22, 444.81, 447.1ϫ, 785.4) . In accordance with previous studies, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] 39 we did not include toe or forefoot amputations that preserved the heel for ambulation. For the main analyses, we classified procedures as either amputation (aboveknee amputation or below-knee amputation) or revascularization (bypass, angioplasty, or stenting).",
